functions.name: Get Data by Query ID
functions.description: Returns query data from Dune Analytics

args.name: Enter Dune Query ID
args.example: e.g. 2034748  for the Dune Query https://dune.com/queries/2034748

args.name: Enter ETH address field from Dune Query
args.example: e.g. “The ETH Address Winner”  for the Dune Query https://dune.com/queries/2034748
args.description: We are fetching the ETH addresses from the dune query. Enter the address field in Dune

functions.name: Get Data by Query ID & Query Parameters
functions.description: Returns query data from Dune Analytics

args.name: Enter Dune Query ID
args.example: e.g. 1618116  for the Dune Query https://dune.com/queries/1618116

args.name: Enter ETH address field from Dune Query
args.example: e.g. “holder”  for the Dune Query https://dune.com/queries/1618116
args.description: We are fetching the ETH addresses from the dune query. Enter the address field in Dune

args.name: Enter Query Parameters
args.example: e.g. {address: '0x3CAaE25Ee616f2C8E13C74dA0813402eae3F496b', blocknumber: '66257668', chain: 'arbitrum'} for the Dune Query https://dune.com/queries/1618116
args.description: We are fetching the ETH addresses from the dune query. Enter the address field in Dune
